rComments: Take her contracts class! Suzy Dunn is easily one of the best instructors I've had in my post-secondary education. Lectures were clear, grading was fair, expectations for exams were transparent. She genuinely wants her students to succeed. Overall a delightful person and I feel lucky to have had her as an instructor.

The structure of the Indigenous content could be a lot more organized for students, but the rest of the material is covered beautifully. Her recaps and slides are super helpful for summaries and outlines. Very helpful even outside the course, and gives great feedback. A lot of readings assigned especially with guest lecturers - beware.
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Get ready to read', 'Accessible outside class']
